{{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Religion and Health | cover = Journal of Religion and Health.jpg | discipline = [[Public health]], [[religious studies]] | editor = Curtis W. Hart | website = https://www.springer.com/public+health/journal/10943 | link1 = http://www.springerlink.com/openurl.asp?genre=issue&issn=0022-4197&issue=current | link1-name = Online access | publisher = [[Springer Science+Business Media]] | country = | abbreviation = J. Religion Health | history = 1961–present | frequency = Quarterly | ISSN = 0022-4197 | eISSN = 1573-6571 | impact = 0.945 | impact-year = 2013 | JSTOR = 00224197 | OCLC = 44707874 | LCCN = 64006093 | CODEN = JRHEAT }} The '''''Journal of Religion and Health''''' is an [[interdisciplinarity|interdisciplinary]] [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by [[Springer Science+Business Media]]. It publishes original articles that deal with [[Mental health|mental]] and [[health|physical health]] in relation to [[religion]] and [[spirituality]] of all kinds. The journal was established in 1961 by the [[Blanton-Peale Institute]].
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed by [[InfoTrac|Academic OneFile]], [[Arts and Humanities Citation Index|Arts & Humanities Citation Index]], [[ATLA Religion Database]], [[Current Contents]]/Social & Behavioral Sciences, Current Contents/Arts and Humanities, [[EMBASE]], [[Journal Citation Reports]]/Social Sciences Edition, [[PsycINFO]], [[PubMed]]/[[MEDLINE]], [[Scopus]], and [[Social Sciences Citation Index]].
==Schizophrenia and possession== In 2014, the journal published a controversial<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.improbable.com/2014/06/02/schizophrenia-caused-by-demons/ |title=Improbable Research » Blog Archive |publisher=[[Annals of Improbable Research|Improbable Research, Inc.]] |date=2014-06-02 |accessdate=2014-06-10}}</ref> article arguing that [[schizophrenia]] could be caused by [[demonic possession]] and that "it would be useful for medical professions to work together with faith healers to define better treatment pathways for schizophrenia".<ref>{{cite journal |doi=10.1007/s10943-012-9673-y|pmid=23269538|title=Schizophrenia or Possession?|journal=Journal of Religion and Health|volume=53|issue=3|pages=773–7|year=2012|last1=Irmak|first1=M. Kemal}}</ref>
